claim.claim-text:
10. A semiconductor device comprising:
a first gate electrode layer over an insulating surface;
a first gate insulating layer covering the first gate electrode layer;
an oxide semiconductor layer including a crystalline region over the first gate insulating layer;
a source electrode layer and a drain electrode layer in electrical contact with the oxide semiconductor layer;
a second gate insulating layer covering the oxide semiconductor layer; and
a second gate electrode layer over the crystalline region with the second gate insulating layer interposed therebetween,
wherein a hydrogen concentration of the oxide semiconductor layer is 5×1019 /cm3 or less, and
wherein the crystalline region includes a crystal whose c-axis is aligned in a direction substantially perpendicular to a surface of the oxide semiconductor layer.
